han Prag made provisional revisions, pending autopsy\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003399_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003399.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\">\n                \u003Cab>\u003C!--Greek or Latin (etc.) text here-->\u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--external apparatus criticus (if applicable)-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>The piece remains formally unpublished, and a new edition will be presented here shortly, pending autopsy\u003C!--commented out pending revision-->\n                    \u003C!--damaged top and right; No proper edition yet. Found in excavatoin in the garden of Hotel Garibaldi, finds smmarised in rhe Antiquarium vol, pp 234-236, and images from vetrina 23 ontaining selection of the material on pp. 239-40, from excavation of 2005. Report in Lo Stretto volume by Tigano does not mention this directly (only the nearby excavation in Piazzetta MezzaLuna, which is partially described in Mylai II, pp. 253-271. (all in contrada Vaccarella). There’s good evidence from these ecavations of fish conservation, and lots of amphorae evidence, Hellenistic and Roman. Inscription only mentioned in the anitquarium volume with photograph.-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Tigano\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2009\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>236 fig.8\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RXD2XUXU\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001560\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001560\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
